    "question": "Angle A and angle B are supplementary. If the measure of angle B is one-third the measure of angle A, what is the measure of angle B?",
    "options": {
      "A": "22.5°",
      "B": "45°",
      "C": "67.5°",
      "D": "135°"
    },
    "correct": "B",
    "source": "generated",
    "canonical_id": "19_001",
    "solution": {
      "strategy": "The sum of the measures of supplementary angles is 180°, so set up an equation using the relationship between angles A and B to solve for B.",
      "steps": [
        "Let A + B = 180° and B = (1/3)A. So A + (1/3)A = 180°, (4/3)A = 180°, A = 135°.",
        "B = 180° - 135° = 45°."
      ],
      "final_answer": "45°"
    }
